# Cloud-Native Proctoring: Frontend-Push Architecture

Transition the proctoring system from **Backend-Pull** (server controls `cv2.VideoCapture`) to **Frontend-Push** (browser owns the camera, sends frame snapshots to the server for analysis).

**Why?** On Hugging Face Spaces (and any cloud host), the Python backend cannot access a webcam — there is no hardware camera. The browser already has `getUserMedia()` access. We let the browser capture frames and POST them to the server.

**Key constraint:** All local development functionality must remain intact. The old `/start` → `/stop` session lifecycle stays the same; only the *camera source* changes.

