### Layer 3 — React Frontend

#### [MODIFY] [ProctoringContext.jsx](file:///c:/Users/acer/Desktop/DL%20Project/client/src/context/ProctoringContext.jsx)

Major changes:
- Use `navigator.mediaDevices.getUserMedia({ video: true })` to acquire the camera stream.
- Store the `MediaStream` in a ref and expose it via context so ProctoringPanel can display it.
- Set up an interval (~1000ms) to:
  1. Draw the current video frame onto a hidden `<canvas>`.
  2. Export as JPEG Base64 (compressed, ~480p).
  3. POST to `/api/proctoring/process_frame`.
  4. Use the response to update `isSafe`, `alertCount`, `detailedMetrics`, etc.
- **Replace the polling interval** (`/api/proctoring/status` every 500ms) — the frame-push response IS the status update. No more separate polling.
- On cleanup, stop the MediaStream tracks.

#### [MODIFY] [ProctoringPanel.jsx](file:///c:/Users/acer/Desktop/DL%20Project/client/src/components/proctoring/ProctoringPanel.jsx)

- Replace `<img src="/api/proctoring/video?t=...">` with `<video ref={...} autoPlay muted playsInline>`.
- Attach the MediaStream from context to the video element via `videoRef.current.srcObject = stream`.
- This gives a smooth 30/60FPS live preview instead of choppy MJPEG.
- Remove `imageLoaded`/`retryCount` state (no longer needed).

#### [MODIFY] [api.js](file:///c:/Users/acer/Desktop/DL%20Project/client/src/services/api.js)

- **Add `processFrame(base64Image)`** to `proctoringAPI` — sends the frame to the Express proxy.

